According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Automotive Press-fit Pin Market was valued at USD 1.02 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 1.34 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 4.1% during the forecast period.
The market is experiencing steady growth as automakers increasingly adopt high-reliability press-fit pin technology for secure mechanical and electrical connections across modern vehicle platforms. Automotive press-fit pins eliminate the need for soldering or welding, providing durable, vibration-resistant, and thermally stable interconnections for critical automotive systems. Growing vehicle electrification, rising production of electric vehicles (EVs), and the expanding integration of advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS) are significantly driving demand for precision-engineered press-fit solutions.
